com.infinityrefactoring.reflections

Class ArrayNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.infinityrefactoring.reflections.ExpressionNode
      • com.infinityrefactoring.reflections.ArrayNode

  • public class ArrayNode
extends ExpressionNode
    Represents an array node of a path expression. An array node is compound by an index and an optional internal node, that can be: a field, a method or an array. Examples of Array node:
    • [0]
    • field[1]
    • [0][1][2][3]
    • methodName()[1]
    • methodName(a, b)[2]
